\c 5  
\s1 Moses repeated for them the Ten Commandments  
\p
\v 1 \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w*/\w I|strong="H3117"\w* \w summoned|strong="H7121"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w people|strong="H8085"\w* \w of|strong="H3117"\w* \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w* \w and|strong="H4872"\w* \w said|strong="H1696"\w* \w to|strong="H1696"\w* \w them|strong="H6213"\w*,  
\p “\w You|strong="H3605"\w* Israeli \w people|strong="H8085"\w*, \w listen|strong="H8085"\w* \w to|strong="H1696"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w rules|strong="H2706"\w* \w and|strong="H4872"\w* \w regulations|strong="H4941"\w* \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w I|strong="H3117"\w* am \w giving|strong="H1696"\w* \w to|strong="H1696"\w* \w you|strong="H3605"\w* \w today|strong="H3117"\w*. \w Learn|strong="H3925"\w* \w them|strong="H6213"\w* \w and|strong="H4872"\w* \w be|strong="H3478"\w* \w sure|strong="H8104"\w* \w to|strong="H1696"\w* \w obey|strong="H8085"\w* \w them|strong="H6213"\w*.  
\v 2 \w When|strong="H3068"\w* \w we|strong="H3068"\w* \w were|strong="H3068"\w* \w at|strong="H3068"\w* Sinai \add Mountain\add*, \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w our|strong="H3068"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w* \w made|strong="H3772"\w* \w an|strong="H3772"\w* \w agreement|strong="H1285"\w* \w with|strong="H5973"\w* us.  
\v 3 \w But|strong="H3588"\w* \w this|strong="H2063"\w* \w agreement|strong="H1285"\w* \w was|strong="H3068"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* \w only|strong="H3588"\w* \w for|strong="H3588"\w* \w our|strong="H3068"\w* ancestors. \w He|strong="H3588"\w* \w made|strong="H3772"\w* \w it|strong="H3588"\w* \w also|strong="H3068"\w* \w for|strong="H3588"\w* \w us|strong="H3588"\w* \w who|strong="H3605"\w* \w are|strong="H3117"\w* \w alive|strong="H2416"\w* \w now|strong="H3117"\w*.  
\v 4 \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w spoke|strong="H1696"\w* \w with|strong="H5973"\w* \w us|strong="H6440"\w* face-to-face \w on|strong="H3068"\w* \w that|strong="H3068"\w* \w mountain|strong="H2022"\w*, \w from|strong="H6440"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* \w middle|strong="H8432"\w* \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* fire.  
\v 5 \w On|strong="H3068"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w day|strong="H6256"\w*, \w I|strong="H3588"\w* \w stood|strong="H5975"\w* between \w your|strong="H3068"\w* ancestors \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w tell|strong="H5046"\w* \w them|strong="H6440"\w* \w what|strong="H1697"\w* \w he|strong="H1931"\w* \w said|strong="H1697"\w*, \w because|strong="H3588"\w* \w they|strong="H3588"\w* \w were|strong="H1697"\w* \w afraid|strong="H3372"\w* \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* fire, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w they|strong="H3588"\w* \w did|strong="H3068"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* \w climb|strong="H5927"\w* \w up|strong="H5927"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* \w mountain|strong="H2022"\w*. \w This|strong="H1931"\w* \w is|strong="H3068"\w* \w what|strong="H1697"\w* \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w said|strong="H1697"\w*:   
\mi
\v 6 ‘\w I|strong="H4714"\w* \w am|strong="H3068"\w* \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w your|strong="H3068"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w*, \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w one|strong="H3068"\w* \w you|strong="H4714"\w* \add worship\add*. \w I|strong="H4714"\w* \w am|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w one|strong="H3068"\w* \w who|strong="H3068"\w* \w brought|strong="H3318"\w* \w you|strong="H4714"\w* \w out|strong="H3318"\w* \w of|strong="H1004"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* land \w of|strong="H1004"\w* \w Egypt|strong="H4714"\w*. \w I|strong="H4714"\w* \w am|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w one|strong="H3068"\w* \w who|strong="H3068"\w* freed \w you|strong="H4714"\w* \w from|strong="H3318"\w* \w being|strong="H3068"\w* \w slaves|strong="H5650"\w* \add there\add*.   
\li1
\v 7  \add You must worship only\add* me; you must not worship any other god.   
\li1
\v 8 You must not carve/make for yourselves any idol that represents anything in the sky or anything that is on the ground or anything that swims in the water.   
\li1
\v 9 You must not bow down to any idol and worship it, because I am Yahweh God, and I ◄am very jealous/want you to worship me only►. I punish those who sin and hate me. I punish not only them, but I will punish ◄their descendants, down to the third and fourth generation/their children and grandchildren and great-grandchildren►.  
\v 10 But I will steadfastly love ◄thousands of generations/all the descendants► of those who love me and obey my commandments (OR, I will love for thousands of generations).   
\li1
\v 11 Do not use/speak my name carelessly (OR, for wrong/evil purposes), because I am Yahweh God, the one whom you \add should worship\add*, and I will certainly punish those who use/speak my name for wrong/evil purposes [LIT].   
\li1
\v 12 Do not forget that the seventh day \add of every week\add* is mine. Dedicate those days to me just like I, Yahweh your God, am commanding you.   
\li1
\v 13 There are six days each week for you to do all your work,  
\v 14 but the seventh day is a rest day, a day dedicated to me, Yahweh your God. On that day you must not do any work. You and your sons and daughters and your male and female slaves must not work. You must not even force your livestock to work, and you must not tell foreigners to work, those who are living in your country. You must allow your slaves to rest on that day just like you do.  
\v 15 Do not forget that you were slaves in Egypt, and that I, Yahweh your God, brought you out from there by my very great power. [DOU, MTY] That is the reason that I am commanding that \add all of\add* you must rest on the seventh/Sabbath day \add each week\add*.   
\li1
\v 16 Honor/Respect your fathers and your mothers, just like I, Yahweh your God, am commanding you, in order that you may live a long time in the land that I, Yahweh your God, will give you, and in order that things will go well for you there.   
\li1
\v 17 Do not murder anyone.   
\li1
\v 18 Do not ◄commit adultery/have sex with anyone other than your spouse►.   
\li1
\v 19 Do not steal anything.   
\li1
\v 20 Do not tell lies about anyone \add when you are speaking in a court\add*.   
\li1
\v 21 Do not ◄covet/desire to have► someone else’s wife, someone else’s house, someone else’s fields, someone else’s male slave or female slave, someone else’s livestock, someone else’s donkeys, or anything else that another person owns.’   
\p
\v 22 \w Those|strong="H3605"\w* \w are|strong="H1697"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w commandments|strong="H1697"\w* \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w spoke|strong="H1696"\w* \w to|strong="H1696"\w* \w your|strong="H3068"\w* ancestors. \w When|strong="H1696"\w* \w they|strong="H3068"\w* \w were|strong="H1697"\w* \w gathered|strong="H5414"\w* \w there|strong="H2022"\w* \w at|strong="H5921"\w* \add the bottom of\add* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w mountain|strong="H2022"\w*, \w he|strong="H3068"\w* \w spoke|strong="H1696"\w* \w with|strong="H3068"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w very|strong="H1419"\w* \w loud|strong="H1419"\w* \w voice|strong="H6963"\w* \w from|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w middle|strong="H8432"\w* \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* fire, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w there|strong="H2022"\w* \w were|strong="H1697"\w* \w dark|strong="H6205"\w* \w clouds|strong="H6051"\w* surrounding \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w mountain|strong="H2022"\w*. \w He|strong="H3068"\w* \w spoke|strong="H1696"\w* \w only|strong="H3605"\w* \w those|strong="H3605"\w* \add ten\add* \w commandments|strong="H1697"\w*, \w no|strong="H3808"\w* \w more|strong="H3254"\w*. \w Then|strong="H1696"\w* \w he|strong="H3068"\w* \w wrote|strong="H3789"\w* \w them|strong="H5414"\w* \w on|strong="H5921"\w* \w two|strong="H8147"\w* stone \w tablets|strong="H3871"\w* \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w gave|strong="H5414"\w* \w them|strong="H5414"\w* \w to|strong="H1696"\w* \w me|strong="H5414"\w*.   
\p
\v 23 \w After|strong="H1961"\w* \w your|strong="H3605"\w* ancestors \w heard|strong="H8085"\w* \add Yahweh’s\add* \w voice|strong="H6963"\w* \w when|strong="H1961"\w* \w he|strong="H3605"\w* spoke \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w them|strong="H7126"\w* \w out|strong="H8432"\w* \w of|strong="H7626"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w darkness|strong="H2822"\w*, \w while|strong="H1961"\w* \w there|strong="H1961"\w* \w was|strong="H1961"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* big fire \w burning|strong="H1197"\w* \w on|strong="H1961"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w mountain|strong="H2022"\w*, \w their|strong="H3605"\w* \w leaders|strong="H7218"\w* \w and|strong="H6963"\w* \w elders|strong="H2205"\w* \w came|strong="H1961"\w* \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w me|strong="H6963"\w*,  
